<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
The Global Human Resources (GHR) group at Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America enables the company to drive revenue through attracting, developing and retaining a world-class workforce.  HR strategy aligns to business strategy to ensure the company has the talent needed to achieve its business objectives.  Key units within Global HR are Staffing, Compensation, Benefits, Shared Services, Leadership Development, Learning, and a team of Generalists.  In addition to advising business leaders, Global HR helps the company deliver a higher standard of working environment, benefits, work/life commitment and satisfaction for our 200,000 associates. 
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<p class="bac">
The Global HR College Leadership and Development Program is a 2-year rotational program designed to create a pipeline of talent that can move into key generalist or specialist areas within Global HR and help drive our business forward into the future.  The program is comprised of 2 job assignments, each lasting 12 months in length.  Throughout the program, participants will:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Develop the skills and core competencies necessary to potentially move into leadership positions upon completion of the 2 year program</li>
	<li>Have a formal support structure including a designated assignment manager, program manager, peer coach, learning curriculum, program events, monthly program meetings, and structured on boarding orientation</li>
	<li>Ongoing feedback on leadership and performance</li>
	<li>Exposure to various HR functions, LOBs and access to various leadership teams through work assignments and networking events</li>
	<li>Own and manage their careers</li>
</ul>
<br>
<h2 class="bac">Entry Program Positions</h2>  
<br>
<h3 class="bac">Leadership Development (LD) Consultant I - responsibilities</h3>  
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Partner with executive management to accelerate strategy implementation and change/build leadership talent to fuel future growth, enhance organizational performance and accelerate learning across the organization</li>
	<li>Design, develop and deliver leadership development innovations to help clients in all businesses drive objectives</li>
	<li>Collaborate with clients to create competitive, innovative leadership development plans that drive short and long term business growth</li>
	<li>Consult with the line of business on key issues including executive and management development, succession planning, key high potentials&#39; development, organizational development, change management and change communications</li>
	<li>Provide expert advice; “create the pull” for a different client agenda; ask the tough questions</li>
	<li>Contract/set clear expectations with clients about project goals, roles, resources, costs, etc.</li>
	<li>Enable clients to reach critical decisions and results through strong group facilitation and process consultation</li>
</ul>
<br>
<h3 class="bac">Learning Consultant I - responsibilities</h3>  
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Assist learning managers and L&amp;LD(Learning and Leadership Development) client team to create end-to-end learning solutions that support and drive business strategy</li>
	<li>Identify skill gaps and define the appropriate solutions</li>
	<li>Assist with the effective implementation of learning solutions, including:</li>
	<ul class="bac">
		<li>Classroom-based learning solution complete with learning objectives, assessments, leaders guide, media support elements, and participant materials for use by the Instructors</li>
		<li>Technology based learning, including web based training, podcasts, etc.</li>
		<li>On-the-job tool (Quick Reference Cards) or job aid for use by the Line of Business (LOB)</li>
	</ul>
	<li>Continuously explore methods and techniques that drive toward the reduction of cycle time in the development of learning solutions</li>
	<li>Conduct performance analysis, assess learning needs within the business and recommend appropriate solutions</li>
	<li>Participate in interpreting effectiveness of training and LOB satisfaction</li>
	<li>Apply adult learning principles to learning solutions</li>
</ul>
<br>
<h3 class="bac">Instructional Designer – responsibilities</h3>  
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Determine learning solutions and components that address knowledge gaps of the target audience</li>
	<li>Validate provided analysis, prescribe, and design appropriate learning solutions employing instructional technologies and modalities including Web Based Training (WBT), Instructor Led Learning (ILT), on-line and paper-based references, and other forms of learning</li>
	<li>Assists the Learning Shared Services management team in driving increased efficiencies in learning solution development</li>
	<li>Continually explore methods and techniques that drive toward the reduction of cycle time for learning solutions</li>
	<li>Conduct a validation of the task, audience, environment, and content analysis</li>
	<li>Prescribe appropriate learning solutions to meet the needs of Business Partners</li>
	<li>Organize high level content and design learning solutions for various delivery methods</li>
	<li>Provide the Development Team the high level concept document for content outlines, learning objectives, and evaluation criteria and work to ensure learning solutions adhere to design specifications and standard of the business</li>
</ul>
<br>
<h3 class="bac">Compensation Consultant I - responsibilities</h3>  
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Design, develop and deliver compensation strategy innovations that help clients across all businesses drive business objectives</li>
	<li>Skillfully interpret survey data for market pricing; chooses relevant information, analyzes and matches job to similar roles in the marketplace</li>
	<li>Modify compensation programs based on changes in business strategy/performance</li>
	<li>Demonstrate in-depth knowledge of incentive plan components (eligibility, performance measures and funding methods)</li>
	<li>Facilitate/drive flawless execution of the year-end incentive process </li>
	<li>Leverage tools, processes, education strategies and HR partners to drive pay for performance adoption</li>
	<li>Change Management: Build commitment to compensation process changes; builds support along the way and works with client group to address issues, obstacles, resistance to change</li>
	<li>Oversee the day-to-day work of the Compensation Analyst</li>
</ul>
<br>
<h3 class="bac">Shared Services Case Manager - responsibilities</h3>  
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Research and prepare formal responses to charges of discrimination by government agencies</li>
	<li>Conduct discrimination investigations</li>
	<li>Conduct sexual harassment investigations</li>
	<li>Respond to DOL claims</li>
	<li>Conduct Work Environment Assessments (WEA) </li>
</ul>
<br>
<h3 class="bac">Shared Services Work Force Communications - responsibilities</h3>  
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Partner successfully with Compensation and Benefits management to develop audience adoption and engagement plans for key initiatives, to enhance organizational programs and to accelerate understanding across the organization</li>
	<li>Design, develop and deliver readiness plans to help clients drive objectives</li>
	<li>Consult with Compensation and Benefits on: new program development, building communications plans to support new programs and developing metrics driven approaches to gauge effectiveness of communications plans</li>
</ul>
<br>
<h3 class="bac">Selection and Assessments – responsibilities</h3>  
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Assist with the development, validation, implementation, and monitoring of employment selection systems and tools throughout the company</li>
	<li>Develop behavioral interview guides and advise clients on utilization of guides in the interview process</li>
	<li>Gather, report and analyze measures of assessment effectiveness, including validation studies, ROI analysis, pass rate and adverse impact reporting; requires the use of statistical tools and established research methods</li>
	<li>Develop job-related, legally defensible screening questions to evaluate minimal qualifications for various jobs</li>
	<li>Provide support for various initiatives led by the Assessment Consultants</li>
</ul>

